<div>
    <div>
        <h1>Types of Questions From Teens</h1>
    </div>
    <div>
        <p>
        How facilitators respond to questions from teens can impact how safe a teen feels in your class, which
        is very important to your teens' learning, application of new knowledge and skills, and social emotional development.
        Facilitators should respond to questions while keeping healthy boundaries in mind and teaching teens how to think,
        not what to think. The vast majority of questions teens ask can be placed into one of 4 categories; each
        category has specific guidelines for how facilitators can respond in a way that supports safe space.
        </p>
    </div>
</div>


<div>
<img src="https://cdn4.iconfinder.com/data/icons/simplicio/128x128/file_add.png" height=35px>
<%= link_to 'Add New Question Type', new_type_path %>
</div>

<div>
    <% @types.each do |type| %>
        <div>
            <h3><%= type.title %></h3>
        </div>
        <div>
            <h4><%= type.description %></h4>
        </div>
        <div>
            <%= type.tips %>
        </div>
        <div>
            <img src="https://cdn4.iconfinder.com/data/icons/web-ui-color/128/Edit-512.png" height=35px>
            <%= link_to 'Edit', edit_type_path(type) %>
        </div>
        <div>
           <img src="https://cdn2.iconfinder.com/data/icons/metro-uinvert-dock/256/Recycle_Bin_Full.png" height=35px>
            <%= link_to 'Delete', type_path(type), method: :delete %>
        </div>
        <div>
            <%= link_to 'Show Associated Questions', type_path(type), method: :get %>
        </div>
    <% end %>
</div>